    &lt;Title&gt;Very Humble and grateful&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Nora Mayes&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;After falling ill very suddenly last October, frightened, in a lot of pain and discomfort, I was sent by my GP to Chapel Allerton Hospital.  The staff, nurses and doctors I cannot thank enough.  My GP was excellent in the first place and my appointment was quick.  The treatment was put in place to get me out of my pain, everything was explained and I was encouraged to ask questions.  I have been treated with respect and dignity all the time.  If I were asked to pay for the treatment given it could not have been better.  Appointments have been good, and ALL staff are kind and considerate.  I am so humbly grateful to have been given my life back again.  Lucky to live in Leeds where these facilities are and thankful to these kind people.  They do their job with a kind word and smile.  Thank you so very much.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
